<item>
            <title>[JDK-8299849] Revert JDK-8294461: wrong effectively final determination by javac</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8299849</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Effectively final handling was changed to be closer to the wording of the JLS under &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8294461&quot; title=&quot;wrong effectively final determination by javac&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8294461&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8294461&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. However, this lead to &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8299416&quot; title=&quot;javac complains about &amp;quot;local variables referenced from an inner class must be final or effectively final&amp;quot; although variable is only assigned once&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8299416&quot;&gt;JDK-8299416&lt;/a&gt;, and it turns out the effectively handling needs more complex consideration, including the specification.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Therefore, the proposal is to revert &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8294461&quot; title=&quot;wrong effectively final determination by javac&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8294461&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8294461&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and reconsider the effectively final handling in a future release, making adjustments as needed.</description>
